# Git Rules

- This is a personal repo — direct commits to `main` are allowed for small, punctual changes; create a branch only for larger multi-step work
- Always use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) style
- When moving files, prefer `git mv` over `mv` whenever possible
- Only use `git push --force-with-lease` instead of `--force`
- Add `| cat` to git commands to prevent interactive mode

# GitHub PR Creation

- Always use the `gh` CLI to create PRs
- Ignore uncommitted and unstaged changes unless explicitly requested
- Ensure branch is created and changes committed before creating PR
- Format PR title as: `<type>(<scope>): <short summary>`
- Build PR description from committed changes
- Use `.github/pull_request_template.md` as base if it exists
- Use a markdown file (e.g., `pr_body.md`) for PR body to avoid formatting issues
- Do not commit `pr_body.md`
